		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/10/20/today-in-small-business-how-hackers-can-stick-businesses-with-huge-phone-bills/" data-title="Today in Small Business: How Hackers Can Stick Businesses With Huge Phone Bills" data-description="Why businesses are pushing back against a travel ban. Why young graduates are headed to places like Buffalo and Cleveland. Does Amazon have too much power?">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>This New York City cook <a href="//mashable.com/2014/10/19/dosa-man-food-cart-nyc/#:">turned</a> a tiny food cart into a culinary triumph.</li>
<li>An <a href="//www.appeal-democrat.com/business/farms-angry-at-labor-department-crackdown/article_b9381a08-5736-11e4-a531-001a4bcf6878.html#.V">attempted crackdown</a> on minimum-wage and child-labor violations at berry farms in the Pacific Northwest has sparked a backlash.</li>
<li>A chocolate maker <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/19/us/chocolate-maker-stays-true-to-his-texas-roots.html?_r=0">stays close to his</a> Texas roots.</li>
<li>More young graduates are choosing to live in cities like <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/20/upshot/where-young-college-graduates-are-choosing-to-live.html">Denver, San Diego, Nashville, Salt Lake City</a> &#8212; and &#8220;even economically troubled places like Buffalo and Cleveland.&#8221;</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Data Security</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here&#8217;s how <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/20/technology/dial-and-redial-phone-hackers-stealing-billions-.html">hackers can stick small businesses</a> with hundreds of thousands of dollars in phone bills.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Employees</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Doctor says no overtime? <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/20/nyregion/doctors-letter-spells-end-of-job-for-pregnant-employee.html">Pregnant worker&#8217;s boss</a> says no job.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Economy</strong></p>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>Is <a href="//www.marketplace.org/topics/wealth-poverty/indie-economics/inflation-problem-look-income-brackets">inflation a problem</a>?</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span id="more-89438"></span></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Travel</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Businesses are <a href="//thehill.com/policy/finance/221150-businesses-quietly-push-back-at-ebola-travel-ban">pushing back</a> against calls by lawmakers to impose a travel ban on three West Africa nations at the center of the Ebola epidemic.</li>
<li>A <a href="//finance.yahoo.com/news/survey-airlines-cheapest-most-comfy-000535001.html?">survey</a> reveals which domestic airlines have the most comfortable economy seats.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Cash Flow</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A pair of recent developments <a href="//www.nasdaq.com/article/good-news-and-bad-for-retirement-savers-20141018-00008#.">brings good news</a> to those with 401(k) accounts but bad news to those with individual retirement accounts.</li>
<li>President Obama signed <a href="//arstechnica.com/business/2014/10/obama-signs-buysecure-initiative-to-speed-emv-adoption-in-the-us/">an executive order</a> to speed the adoption of E.M.V.-standard cards in the United States, which would require credit card companies to do away with the common magnetic stripe cards. (The next day, the presidentâs <a href="//www.csmonitor.com/USA/DC-Decoder/Decoder-Buzz/2014/1017/Obama-credit-card-declined-Does-he-need-to-get-out-more-video">credit card</a> was declined.)</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here&#8217;s how a Cuban bakery competes with a nearby <a href="//www.smallbiztechnology.com/archive/2014/10/cuban-bakery-beat-dunkin-donuts-niche-marketing.html/">Dunkin Donuts</a>.</li>
<li>And here&#8217;s how Merrill Lynch <a href="//contentmarketinginstitute.com/2014/10/merril-lynch-uses-content-mapping/">uses content mapping</a> to reach affluent Americans.</li>
<li>Research shows e-mail marketers are <a href="//www.mobilemarketingwatch.com/email-marketing-consumers-love-to-hate-it-but-its-getting-better-45585/">getting better</a> at what they do, but most people still have a love/hate relationship with e-mail.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Social Media</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>It looks like Twitterâs <a href="//www.fastcompany.com/3037277/most-innovative-companies/dont-like-twitters-recommended-tweets-too-bad-theyre-here-to-stay">recommended tweets</a> are here to stay.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Finance</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Wells Fargo announces <a href="//www.latinpost.com/articles/23790/20141018/spanish-text-banking-offered-speaking-customers-helping-small-business-owners.htm">a new plan</a> designed to meet the needs of Hispanic small-business owners.</li>
<li>Venture capital firms <a href="//www.finsmes.com/2014/10/venture-capital-9-9bn-invested-in-1023-deals-in-q3-2014.html?">invested $9.9 billion</a> in 1,023 deals in the third quarter of 2014.</li>
<li>A financial adviser warns of the risks of <a href="//www.hometownlife.com/story/news/local/2014/10/18/losses-bloom-money-advice-investing/17449593/">investing in a small business</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Retail</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="//www.infozine.com/news/stories/op/storiesView/sid/60125/">Sexual harassment</a> is a problem in the restaurant industry, according to a report.</li>
<li>AmazonFresh <a href="//www.capitalotc.com/amazonfresh-online-grocery-service-debuts-in-brooklyn/24557/?">debuts its</a> online grocery service in Brooklyn.</li>
<li>Paul Krugman says <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/20/opinion/paul-krugman-amazons-monopsony-is-not-ok.html">Amazon has too much power</a> &#8212; and is abusing it.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Entrepreneurship</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>EasyJetâs founder <a href="//www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2797949/after-cheap-flights-hotels-s-easyshop-airline-boss-unveils-cashless-supermarket.html">plans to start</a> a cashless budget supermarket.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around The World</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Cuba&#8217;s <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/20/opinion/cubas-impressive-role-on-ebola.html">efforts combating Ebola</a> in West Africa are putting the contributions of other countries to shame.</li>
<li>Tens of thousands of union members <a href="//www.theguardian.com/world/2014/oct/18/tens-thousands-uk-streets-pay-protest-march-union">take to the streets</a> in the United Kingdom in a pay protest.</li>
<li>In Germany, <a href="//www.reuters.com/article/2014/10/18/us-germany-railway-strike-idUSKCN0I70AZ20141018?">train workers</a> and <a href="//www.reuters.com/article/2014/10/19/us-germany-strike-lufthansa-idUSKCN0I80TB20141019">Lufthansa pilots</a> strike.</li>
<li>Small-business owners say France is <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/small-business-owners-explain-why-france-is-a-nation-in-decline-2014-10">a nation in decline</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Technology</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>As Apple Pay is released, here&#8217;s <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/google-wallet-mobile-payments-2014-10">what&#8217;s going on</a> with Google Wallet.</li>
</ul>
